articles.author: Maya Gebeily, Maayan Lubell
articles.description: There were no immediate reports of casualties. Israeli authorities said air sirens were activated in areas southeast of Tel Aviv.
articles.title: Hezbollah says launches volley of rockets into Israel, Blinken returns seeking ceasefire

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Turkey said on Wednesday that a deadly attack was carried out at the headquarters of Turkish Aerospace Industries (TUSAS) near Ankara, while media reported a loud explosion at the site and showed footage of an exchange of gunfire there.
articles.title: Turkey says some dead, injured after attack at state aviation site

articles.author: Christopher Bing, A.j. Vicens
articles.description: The report links the group, Cotton Sandstorm, to Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps.
articles.title: Iranian hacker group focuses on US election websites, media, ahead of vote, Microsoft says

articles.author: Khalid Abdelaziz, Reade Levinson, Filipp Lebedev
articles.description: A plane downed in Sudan's North Darfur state had Russian crew members and was being used by the army to resupply the besieged city of al-Fashir, according to the opposing faction and documents it said were found in the wreckage.
articles.title: Exclusive: Plane downed in Darfur with suspected Russian crew was supplying army, rivals say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Biden administration is trying to provide Ukraine with $10 billion in military aid as part of its $20 billion commitment to the country under a $50 billion loan coordinated with the G7 and European Union, the White House National Security Council said on Wednesday.
articles.title: US govt wants half of its $20 billion loan to Ukraine to be military aid

articles.author: Felix Onuah
articles.description: Nigerian President Bola Tinubu has reshuffled his 45-member cabinet, naming seven new members, sacking five and swapping 10 others, a spokesperson said on Wednesday.
articles.title: Nigeria's Tinubu names seven ministers, sacks five in cabinet reshuffle

articles.author: Linda So
articles.description: A man accused of selling sex videos of a 16-year-old Florida girl on the adults-only website OnlyFans pleaded no contest to child abuse.
articles.title: OnlyFans user sentenced to five years in child abuse case

articles.author: James Redmayne, Catarina Demony
articles.description: The leaders of the Commonwealth group of nations will meet at a welcome banquet in Samoa in the South Pacific on Thursday, with climate change and reparations for Britain's role in the transatlantic slave trade both likely to be on the agenda.
articles.title: Commonwealth nations to discuss slavery, climate change at Samoa summit

articles.author: Kanishka Singh
articles.description: Over 60 Democratic lawmakers from the U.S. House of Representatives wrote to President Joe Biden on Wednesday, urging him to use Washington's leverage with Pakistan to secure the release of jailed former Prime Minister Imran Khan.
articles.title: Dozens of US lawmakers call for release of former Pakistan PM Imran Khan

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Romania's radar systems detected two separate signals, likely from drones, breaching its national airspace that scrambled fighter jets did not see, the country's defence ministry said late on Wednesday, in a third such incident in less than a week.
articles.title: Romanian radar picks up two likely drone signals breaching territory, ministry says
